                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14428705" author="phh" created="Tue, 31 Aug 2010 01:55:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s seems like the compiler gets the whole string &quot;-Xmaxerrs 1000&quot; as an argument, and not the working version with the argument and value pair of &quot;-Xmaxerrs&quot; &quot;1000&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the AbstractCompilerMojo there is a line about creating the creation of the commandLine:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;String[] cl = compiler.createCommandLine( compilerConfiguration );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And then loops through the String Array, but when setting the &quot;&amp;lt;compilerArgument&amp;gt;-Xmaxerrs 1000&amp;lt;/compilerArgument&amp;gt;&quot; the inner content is considered a single argument, and separation between arguments and values are a single space &quot; &quot;. I think that it&apos;s escaping the spaces within the compilerArgument. I have tried &quot;&amp;lt;compilerArgument&amp;gt;-verbose -help&amp;lt;/compilerArgument&amp;gt;&quot; and that gives the same result. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is tested on Mac OS X.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428623" author="phh" created="Tue, 31 Aug 2010 02:53:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same problem. &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Escaping Space &amp;quot; &amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; in compilerArgument&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428652" author="phh" created="Tue, 31 Aug 2010 02:55:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicates &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MCOMPILER-106&quot; title=&quot;&amp;lt;compilerArgument&amp;gt;-Xlint -Xlint:-path&amp;lt;/compilerArgument&amp;gt; argument quoting problem&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MCOMPILER-106&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MCOMPILER-106&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428719" author="phh" created="Tue, 7 Sep 2010 04:15:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This problem also exists for Windows.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428681" author="pthivent" created="Tue, 7 Sep 2010 05:36:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Affects GNU/Linux too (I guess the problem is not platform dependent).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428641" author="phh" created="Thu, 9 Sep 2010 17:41:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A patch that informs the user if there is a white-space within the &amp;lt;compilerArgument&amp;gt; and a explanation in the FAQ segment of site. Added a parameter to turn the warning off.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The faq text may need checking.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428672" author="rfscholte" created="Sun, 28 Aug 2011 14:55:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I still doubt whether this should be a legal value or not. If it is, the value should be splitted respecting escaped chars and quotes to pass it as separate arguments.&lt;br/&gt;
On the other hand: the parameter says compilerArgument (singular, not plural) so only 1 could be expected.&lt;br/&gt;
Right now it seems it is not possible to add more than one argument like this, so I&apos;m thinking of &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; supporting multiple arguments for this parameter.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll improve the documentation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428727" author="rfscholte" created="Sun, 28 Aug 2011 16:38:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1162597&amp;amp;view=rev&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;rev. 1162597&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17978802" author="olamy" created="Mon, 16 Jun 2025 11:11:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-compiler-plugin/issues/439&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-compiler-plugin#439&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
